snippet: Two reports raised expectations on Wall Street that the Federal Reserve might delay increasing interest rates until early 2016, rather than the middle of next year, to keep support for the economy in place.
lead_paragraph: Two reports raised expectations on Wall Street that the Federal Reserve might delay increasing interest rates until early 2016, rather than the middle of next year, to keep support for the economy in place.

headline.main: Jitters Creep Up After Economic Data Disappoints
